My major opus in the field of criticism is a critical biography of NIKOLAI GOGOL (New Directions Publ., 1944).

In 1941 I read at the Annual Meeting of the New England Modern Language Association an essay which was later published in the Bulletin of the organization under the title THE CREATIVE WRITER. An article THE LERMONTO